sentences: After a brief period performing opera professionally after graduation, she moved back to the New York City to pursue songwriting and jazz in 2009.
Zuraitis released her first album Spread the Word in 2008, featuring Luques Curtis, Zaccai Curtis and Winard Harper.
Her most recent album All Wandering Hearts released in July 2020.
Recent touring projects have included Generations of Her, featuring songs by female composers from 1924 to the present.
In 2019, she and Pugach received a co-nomination for a Grammy Award for their arrangement of Dolly Parton's "Jolene."
